  Filename: [33m/hypothesis-6.131.0/src/hypothesis/internal/conjecture/utils.py[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m170 | [0m[35m    We maintain the following invariants to try to produce good shrinks:[0m
[30;1m171 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m172 | [0m[35m    1. The table is in lexicographic (base, alternate) order, so that choosing[0m
[30;1m173 | [0m[35m       an earlier value in the list always lowers (or at least leaves[0m
[30;1m174 | [0m[35m       unchanged) the value.[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35m    2. base[i] < alternate[i], so that shrinking the draw always results in[0m
[30;1m176 | [0m[35m       shrinking the chosen element.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m234[0m[34m of [0m[33m951[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/hypothesis-6.131.0/src/hypothesis/internal/conjecture/utils.py[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m    http://www.keithschwarz.com/darts-dice-coins/ for a good explanation.[0m
[30;1m164 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m165 | [0m[35m    The general idea is that we store a table of triples (base, alternate, p).[0m
[30;1m166 | [0m[35m    base. We then pick a triple uniformly at random, and choose its alternate[0m
[30;1m167 | [0m[35m    value with probability p and else choose its base value. The triples are[0m
[30;1m168 | [0m[35m    chosen so that the resulting mixture has the right distribution.[0m
[30;1m169 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m320 | [0m[35m        # conclusion: If we've called the underlying test function at[0m
[30;1m321 | [0m[35m        # least self.max_stall times since the last time we shrunk,[0m
[30;1m322 | [0m[35m        # it's time to stop shrinking.[0m
[30;1m323 | [0m[35m        self.max_stall = 200[0m
[30;1m324 | [0m[35m        self.initial_calls = self.engine.call_count[0m

[30;1m186 | [0m[35m    Shrink passes need to be written so as to be robust against[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35m    change in the underlying shrink target. It is generally safe[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35m    to assume that the shrink target does not change prior to the[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35m    point of first modification - e.g. if you change no bytes at[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35m    index ``i``, all spans whose start is ``<= i`` still exist,[0m
[30;1m191 | [0m[35m    as do all blocks, and the data object is still of length[0m
[30;1m192 | [0m[35m    ``>= i + 1``. This can only be violated by bad user code which[0m
[30;1m193 | [0m[35m    relies on an external source of non-determinism.[0m

[30;1m100 | [0m[35m    dependent strategies until we reach a fixed point.[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m    The approach taken roughly follows that in section 4.2 of Adams,[0m

[30;1m372 | [0m[35m    to reorder the list to try to get lucky this way as often as possible.[0m
[30;1m373 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m374 | [0m[35m    There are various heuristics we could use for this, and it's not clear[0m
[30;1m375 | [0m[35m    which are best. We use the simplest, which is that every time we find[0m
[30;1m376 | [0m[35m    an item we move it to the "front" (actually the back in our implementation[0m
[30;1m377 | [0m[35m    because we iterate in reverse) of the list.[0m
[30;1m378 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m367 | [0m[35m    A self-organising list is a collection which we want to retrieve items[0m
[30;1m368 | [0m[35m    that satisfy some predicate from. There is no faster way to do this than[0m
[30;1m369 | [0m[35m    a linear scan (as the predicates may be arbitrary), but the performance[0m
[30;1m370 | [0m[35m    of a linear scan can vary dramatically - if we happen to find a good item[0m
[30;1m371 | [0m[35m    on the first try it's O(1) after all. The idea of a self-organising list is[0m
[30;1m372 | [0m[35m    to reorder the list to try to get lucky this way as often as possible.[0m
[30;1m373 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m64 | [0m[35m# other array/tensor libraries. Historically these strategies were built for the[0m

[30;1m178 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m179 | [0m[35m    def restore_all() -> None:[0m
